Source: bottledwater
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Sam Stokes <me@samstokes.co.uk>
Build-Depends:
    debhelper (>= 9), pkg-config,
    postgresql-server-dev-all (>= 148~),
    libpq-dev, libsnappy-dev, libjansson-dev,
    libcurl4-openssl-dev, libavro-dev, libavro, libjansson4,
    librdkafka-dev (>> 0.8.5), librdkafka1 (>> 0.8.5)
Standards-Version: 3.9.5
Homepage: https://github.com/confluentinc/bottledwater-pg
#Vcs-Git: git://anonscm.debian.org/collab-maint/bottledwater.git
#Vcs-Browser: http://anonscm.debian.org/?p=collab-maint/bottledwater.git;a=summary

Package: bottledwater
Architecture: any
Depends:
    ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends},
    libpq5, libsnappy1, libjansson4, curl, libavro, librdkafka1 (>> 0.8.4)
Description: Bottled Water, Change Data Capture from PostgreSQL to Kafka.
 Bottled Water uses PostgreSQL's logical replication feature to replicate
 databases in real-time into Apache's Kafka messaging-system.  This Change Data
 Capture system can publish your relational database updates throughout your
 systems.
 .
 This package contains the replication daemon. It connects to
 a PostgreSQL 9.4+ server with the postgresql-9.x-bottledwater
 extension package installed and Kafka.

